  "prompt": "Why are blue and red neon lights illegal or restricted for commercial uses in Colombia?",
  "response": "In Colombia, the use of blue and red neon lights for commercial purposes is restricted primarily for safety and regulatory reasons. These colors are often associated with emergency vehicles, such as police cars and ambulances. To prevent confusion and ensure public safety, regulations prohibit the use of these colors in commercial signage and lighting. \n\nThe intention behind this restriction is to maintain clear visual signals for emergency services and to avoid any potential misinterpretation of a commercial establishment as an emergency service. Additionally, the regulations aim to promote uniformity and order in urban environments, contributing to better overall traffic and personal safety.\n\nThese restrictions can vary by municipality, so it's essential for businesses to check local regulations before installing specific lighting.",
